    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="497"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d497">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/784.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Smith</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 30, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Impress upon de facto authorities in Port au Prince and upon those in other parts
                    of the Republic, through consuls and consular <pb facs="0453" n="337"
                        xml:id="pg_337"/> agents, the necessity of complying with national
                    obligations with respect to assignment of customs funds for the payment of
                    definite debts. Also impress upon them that there must be no diversion of public
                    moneys required for present obligations. French Government is making similar
                    representations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
